 she invites us to change the way Muslim immigrants, and especially women, are depicted in both news reports and scholarly research. Islam and Me is a meditation on our multireligious, multiethnic, and multilingual reality, as well as an exploration of how we might reimagine national culture and identity so that they become more diverse, inclusive, and anti-racist.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCultural pluralism. 0aImmigrants' writingsxHistory and criticism. 0aIslamophobia. 0aMuslimszNon-Islamic countries. 0aSex discrimination against women. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / General.2bisacsh  amuslim, islam, religion, immigration, migration, emigration, expat, gender, culture, race, language, italy, discrimination, islamphobia, xenophobia, assimilation, politics, policy, women, diaspora, african, identity, belonging, italian, translation.1 aBrioni, Simone, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrioni, Simone, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBurdett, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFazel, Shirin Ramzanali, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRamzanali Fazel, Shirin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079130340uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197883585640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978835856423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978835856/original  a978-3-11-079130-3  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles